#: ../../../reference/random/bit_generators/mt19937.rst:2
msgid "Mersenne Twister (MT19937)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:2
msgid "Container for the Mersenne Twister pseudo-random number generator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:20
msgid "**seed**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:-1
msgid "{None, int, array_like[ints], SeedSequence}, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:8
msgid ""
"A seed to initialize the `BitGenerator`. If None, then fresh, unpredictable "
"entropy will be pulled from the OS. If an ``int`` or ``array_like[ints]`` is "
"passed, then it will be passed to `SeedSequence` to derive the initial "
"`BitGenerator` state. One may also pass in a `SeedSequence` instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:23
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:24
msgid ""
"``MT19937`` provides a capsule containing function pointers that produce "
"doubles, and unsigned 32 and 64- bit integers [R312276d80bfa-1]_. These are "
"not directly consumable in Python and must be consumed by a ``Generator`` or "
"similar object that supports low-level access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:29
msgid ""
"The Python stdlib module \"random\" also contains a Mersenne Twister pseudo-"
"random number generator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:32
msgid "**State and Seeding**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:34
msgid ""
"The ``MT19937`` state vector consists of a 624-element array of 32-bit "
"unsigned integers plus a single integer value between 0 and 624 that indexes "
"the current position within the main array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:38
msgid ""
"The input seed is processed by `SeedSequence` to fill the whole state. The "
"first element is reset such that only its most significant bit is set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:41
msgid "**Parallel Features**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:43
msgid ""
"The preferred way to use a BitGenerator in parallel applications is to use "
"the `SeedSequence.spawn` method to obtain entropy values, and to use these "
"to generate new BitGenerators:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:51
msgid ""
"Another method is to use `MT19937.jumped` which advances the state as-if :"
"math:`2^{128}` random numbers have been generated ([R312276d80bfa-1]_, "
"[R312276d80bfa-2]_). This allows the original sequence to be split so that "
"distinct segments can be used in each worker process. All generators should "
"be chained to ensure that the segments come from the same sequence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:66
msgid "**Compatibility Guarantee**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:68
msgid ""
"``MT19937`` makes a guarantee that a fixed seed will always produce the same "
"random integer stream."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:72
msgid "References"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:73
msgid ""
"Hiroshi Haramoto, Makoto Matsumoto, and Pierre L'Ecuyer, \"A Fast Jump Ahead "
"Algorithm for Linear Recurrences in a Polynomial Space\", Sequences and "
"Their Applications - SETA, 290--298, 2008."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._mt19937.MT19937:76
msgid ""
"Hiroshi Haramoto, Makoto Matsumoto, Takuji Nishimura, François Panneton, "
"Pierre L'Ecuyer, \"Efficient Jump Ahead for F2-Linear Random Number "
"Generators\", INFORMS JOURNAL ON COMPUTING, Vol. 20, No. 3, Summer 2008, pp. "
"385-390."
msgstr ""

